        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">According to “Ullmann's encyclopedia of industrial chemistry”, version published in 2000, the global market of methylamines is estimated to break down as follows: 24% methylamine, 57% dimethylamine, and 19% trimethylamine. In a subsequent edition, version published in 2012, the global production capacity of methylamines was reported, amounting to 1'000'000'000 kg. Hence, the global production volume of dimethylamine, in 2012, was estimated to be 570'000'000 kg.
References: 
van Gysel, A.B. and Musin, W. (2000). Methylamines. In Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, (Ed.). &lt;https://doi.org/10.1002/14356007.a16_535&gt;
van Gysel, A.B. and Musin, W. (2011). Methylamines. In Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, (Ed.). &lt;https://doi.org/10.1002/14356007.a16_535.pub2&gt;
</productionVolumeComment>
